window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From multi-million copy seller, K. L. Slater comes another breath-taking thriller, narrated by Claudia Jessie (star of </b><b><i>Bridgerton</i></b><b> &amp; </b><b><i>Line of Duty</i></b><b>)</b></p> <p><i>All she has to do is pretend to be his girlfriend…</i></p> <p>Alicia has left her young son and sister to chase a better life in London. But she’s not just chasing opportunity, she’s running from the truth.</p> <p>At the Orbit, an elite enclave towering above the city where the great and the good come to play, Alicia waits tables, watching everything.</p> <p>When the charismatic owner of The Orbit offers her a deal - pretend to be her girlfriend in return for a salary and an apartment - Alicia accepts. After all, it’s only pretend … until it’s not.</p> <p>Soon, Alicia is living the life she’s always dreamed of — but behind the flawless façade, something is deeply wrong and some deals cannot be broken. As her past begins to creep towards her, Alicia thought she was the only one playing a game.</p> <p>It turns out she wasn’t alone…</p>"; 
